  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing community capacity to respond to HIV/ AIDS in Western  Equatoria State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This 12 month project will continue to contribute to Western Equatoria State&#x2019;s HIV and AIDS framework by raising awareness among rural communities.  The aim is to increase community knowledge on how to reduce and prevent new HIV transmissions, especially among the most at-risk populations (young people and women men and children) The project will adopt a strong media strategy as a method of reaching the wider public. There will also be an integrated element of livelihoods through agriculture components, in order to provide better nutrition to PLHA.  It will also enhance asset building and income generation which will help the support groups meet their immediate costs, such as transport to access treatment. Income generation activities will also help them run individual business and access markets.  As a result of this project there will be increased community awareness on HIV and AIDS prevention, care and support, increased advocacy and networking around HIV and AIDS issues, increased knowledge on nutrition, increased asset bases and household income leading to increased access to treatment, strengthened capacities of communities, HIV and AIDS structures and support groups, and an overall increased appreciation of HIV and AIDS issues contributing towards a reduction of stigma  and discrimination  hence  community acceptance of PLWHA.</narrative>
  </description>
